Bayer to Maintain Research Spending Steady in 2012, FTD Reports

-- B y   R a i n e r   B u e r g i n
-- 
2011-02-17T19:56:09Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-17/bayer-to-maintain-research-spending-steady-in-2012-ftd-reports.html
Bayer AG will keep its research-and-
development spending steady next year at around 3 billion euros
($4.1 billion), Financial Times Deutschland reported, citing an
agreement between the company and its works council.  To contact the reporters on this story:
Rainer Buergin in Berlin at 
 rbuergin1@bloomberg.net ;  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James Hertling at 
